The '''brown-winged kingfisher''' ('''''Pelargopsis amauroptera''''') is a species of [[bird]] in the subfamily [[Halcyoninae]].

It is found along the north and eastern coasts of the [[Bay of Bengal]], occurring in the countries of [[Bangladesh]], [[India]], [[Malaysia]], [[Myanmar]] and [[Thailand]].<ref name="iucn status 16 November 2021" /> In India, it has been mainly reported from the Sundarbans region but records from further south near Chilka exist.<ref>{{cite journal|author1=Daniel, JC |author2=Hussain, SA |year=1974|title= The Brownwinged Storkbilled Kingfisher ''Pelargopsis amauroptera'' (Pearson) in Orissa|journal= J. Bombay Nat. Hist. Soc. |volume=71| issue=2|pages=304–305}}</ref>

Its natural [[habitat]] is subtropical or tropical mangrove [[forest]]s.
